00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:39,110
We can mostly focus by thinking

291
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:41,140
about quarks themselves if we like.

292
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:45,310
And the statement that there's a baryon excess is the statement

293
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:49,140
that there were in the early universe more quarks than anti-quarks.

294
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:51,150
The number of quarks and anti-quarks separately were

295
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:52,940
about the same as the number of photons.

296
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:58,420
And so the question is how it got that way.

297
00:10:58,860 --> 00:10:59,420
Okay,

298
00:10:59,420 --> 00:11:03,540
let's suppose for the moment that baryon number is one.

299
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:03,780
The number of quarks in the universe is one.

300
00:11:03,780 --> 00:11:03,830
What's the difference between

301
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:03,880
baryon number and electron number?

302
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:04,780
The difference between baryon number and electron number

303
00:11:04,780 --> 00:11:05,680
is that baryon number is like electric charge.

304
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:08,370
One of the things about

305
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:10,400
electric charge is that it's conserved.

306
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,200
It doesn't change with time.

307
00:11:12,580 --> 00:11:13,400
Now,

308
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:16,800
baryon number is not like electric charge.

309
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:22,500
Electric charge is the source of coulomb forces,

310
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,940
long range electric fields,

311
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:29,360
which create long range electrostatic forces.

312
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:33,520
Baryon number itself is not like electric charge.

313
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:35,600
It's not a source of

314
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,680
some kind of coulomb type force.

315
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:38,260
Of course,

316
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:40,940
the protons are electrically charged.

317
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:42,140
Therefore,

318
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:46,820
they make conventional coulomb forces between each other.

319
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:47,920
They make electric fields.

320
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:51,140
The neutrons are not electrically charged.

321
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:52,700
They don't make electric fields.

322
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:55,540
So what we would say is

323
00:11:55,540 --> 00:11:57,720
it's the charge of the proton,

324
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,620
not the baryon number of it,

325
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:01,860
which is creating any kind of long range field.

326
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:07,480
And baryon number itself may be conserved.

327
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,700
It may truly be conserved,

328
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:11,080
but it is not exactly like electric charge.

329
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:14,840
It doesn't exhibit this tendency to make long range forces.

330
00:12:15,940 --> 00:12:16,660
All right.

331
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:18,040
But suppose it's conserved.

332
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,540
Suppose it's conserved.

333
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:26,060
Then if there is ever an excess in the beginning,

334
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:26,520
let's say,

335
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,000
of the universe,

336
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:27,820
whatever that means,

337
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:30,520
then there will always be an excess.

338
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:34,080
And that excess will be sort of frozen in.

339
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:37,400
If you change the number of quarks,

340
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:40,380
you must change the number of anti-quarks by

341
00:12:40,380 --> 00:12:43,360
the same amount if baryon number is conserved.

342
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,160
And what's more,

343
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:46,840
experimentally,

344
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:49,800
baryon number appears to be highly conserved.

345
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:52,440
Nobody has ever seen a proton disappear.

346
00:12:54,020 --> 00:12:56,900
We can talk more about experiments which search

347
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:59,780
for the decay of protons and so forth.

348
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:02,620
But the first approximation in our world,

349
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:06,280
protons are extremely stable.

350
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:07,520
What could they decay to?

351
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:08,260
Let's ask a question.

352
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:09,060
What could they...

353
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:10,880
Suppose a proton was to decay.

354
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,000
What could it decay to?

355
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:16,480
It must decay to things which are lighter than itself.

356
00:13:18,060 --> 00:13:18,580
Okay.

357
00:13:19,660 --> 00:13:21,460
It must decay to something

358
00:13:21,460 --> 00:13:23,260
which has a positive electric charge.

359
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:26,320
So if a proton were to decay...

360
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:28,040
And if we want to

361
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:29,760
assume that whatever it decays to...

362
00:13:29,780 --> 00:13:30,620
is stable,

363
00:13:30,620 --> 00:13:33,880
there's really only one thing that it could decay to.

364
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,330
It could decay to a

365
00:13:36,330 --> 00:13:38,540
positron and something electrically neutral.

366
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:43,000
A proton could decay.

367
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:46,620
A proton could disappear and become a positron.

368
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,500
That conserves electric charge.

369
00:13:48,580 --> 00:13:49,540
It doesn't conserve energy.

370
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,500
A positron is much,

371
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,580
much lighter than a proton.

372
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:56,100
But it would compensate by giving off a neutral particle.

373
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,320
What kind of neutral particle is around?

374
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,580
Photons.

375
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:01,980
Photons are a prime candidate.

376
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:09,400
So a decay possibility for the proton would be...

377
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:09,980
Proton,

378
00:14:09,980 --> 00:14:11,560
I'll draw it as a kind of Feynman diagram.

379
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:15,200
A proton moving along would decay to a photon,

380
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,420
which we'll call gamma.

381
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,300
Photons are typically called gamma.

382
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,760
And an electron antiparticle,

383
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:22,360
E+.

384
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,980
That's a possible thing that could happen.

385
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:28,300
And we don't really know any data.

386
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,320
There's a deep fundamental reason why it can't happen.

387
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:32,820
And maybe it does happen.

388
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:34,360
We're going to talk about whether it does happen.

389
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:34,820
In fact,

390
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:35,600
we think it does happen.

391
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:39,180
But for whatever reason...

392
00:14:39,180 --> 00:14:40,820
What about a neutrino?

393
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:42,060
No,

394
00:14:42,060 --> 00:14:43,320
it can't decay to a...

395
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,800
You mean a positron neutrino?

396
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:45,380
No,

397
00:14:45,380 --> 00:14:45,740
no good.

398
00:14:45,860 --> 00:14:46,440
No good.

399
00:14:46,660 --> 00:14:46,900
Okay.

400
00:14:47,660 --> 00:14:50,060
A neutrino is a fermion.

401
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:53,550
Two fermions make a boson

402
00:14:53,550 --> 00:14:55,800
and a proton is a fermion.

403
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:58,720
So whatever the proton decays to,

404
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,590
it must decay to something

405
00:15:00,590 --> 00:15:02,460
with an odd number of fermions.

406
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:06,960
So it can't decay into a positron and a neutrino.

407
00:15:07,380 --> 00:15:07,980
Right.

408
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:08,520
Yeah.

409
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:11,800
If a baryon number really was conserved,

410
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:14,380
it would correspond to a symmetry of some sort.

411
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:14,760
Yes.

412
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:16,780
Was there a candidate for that

413
00:15:16,780 --> 00:15:18,660
or has no one ever found one?

414
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:19,820
You can always...

415
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:22,060
Given any conserved quantity,

416
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:24,460
you can always make up a symmetry

417
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:26,040
that...

418
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:27,960
But then you can say,

419
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:28,180
well,

420
00:15:28,180 --> 00:15:29,460
all right.

421
00:15:30,820 --> 00:15:32,400
Is it really a symmetry?

422
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:34,280
And the way to test it is always

423
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,940
to ask whether the baryon number is conserved.

424
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:37,760
So it's a little bit circular.

425
00:15:38,780 --> 00:15:39,380
But yes,

426
00:15:39,380 --> 00:15:39,780
you're right.

427
00:15:39,860 --> 00:15:41,860
If the baryon number was conserved,

428
00:15:41,860 --> 00:15:43,160
it would correspond to a symmetry.

429
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,400
And if it's not conserved,

430
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,180
it doesn't correspond to a symmetry.

431
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:47,360
Okay.

432
00:15:47,460 --> 00:15:47,760
Yeah.

433
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:49,600
Is there...

434
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:52,470
Do you think about part was

435
00:15:52,470 --> 00:15:54,440
decaying and part was not decaying?

436
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:57,970
Part was annihilating with each other sort

437
00:15:57,970 --> 00:16:01,500
of different things like a proton can annihilate

438
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:06,420
with a positive...with a negative proton.

439
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:06,900
Yes.

440
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,330
So that...is that...can you think of

441
00:16:09,330 --> 00:16:11,660
that as a decay or not?

442
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:12,180
No,

443
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:13,020
that's not a decay.

444
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,520
It's not a decay of the proton.

445
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:17,680
It's just called annihilation of a proton.

446
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:20,240
But the important point here is

447
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,620
that the baryon number doesn't change.

448
00:16:22,620 --> 00:16:26,040
Three quarks and three anti-quarks came together.

449
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:30,500
The sum total...the baryon number is zero.

450
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,440
And afterwards,

451
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,910
it's just a bunch of photons

452
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:35,380
and the baryon number is still zero.

453
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:36,320
So,

454
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:36,780
right.

455
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:39,140
So that's a fair question,

456
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:41,110
but it does...and you could call

457
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:43,080
it a decay if you wanted to,

458
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:47,060
but it wouldn't correspond to a...right.

459
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:48,240
Okay.

460
00:16:48,420 --> 00:16:52,580
So for whatever reason...and we don't know the reason.

461
00:16:52,580 --> 00:16:53,920
We don't know the reason really fully.

462
00:16:55,370 --> 00:16:59,240
The standard model does not permit this decay incidentally.

463
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:01,420
It doesn't happen in the standard model.

464
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:04,724
But there are versions or extensions of

465
00:17:04,724 --> 00:17:07,220
the standard model which are perfectly viable

466
00:17:08,099 --> 00:17:11,119
in which this process could happen.

467
00:17:12,099 --> 00:17:12,839
Now,

468
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:14,980
one thing we know about it immediately,

469
00:17:14,980 --> 00:17:19,319
the decay rate of the proton cannot be very large.

470
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:21,880
Our protons have been around for...

471
00:17:22,579 --> 00:17:24,339
15 billion years or whatever it is,

472
00:17:24,339 --> 00:17:25,920
13.7 billion years,

473
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,460
and they haven't disappeared on us.

474
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,570
So if the decay time of the

475
00:17:30,570 --> 00:17:33,340
proton were a microsecond or even faster,

476
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:35,620
which particle physics might permit,

477
00:17:35,620 --> 00:17:38,640
the protons just wouldn't be here anymore.

478
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:42,180
So the lifetime of the proton is at least very,

479
00:17:42,180 --> 00:17:42,540
very,

480
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:43,080
very long.

481
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:44,920
But in fact,

482
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:45,800
it's much,

483
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:48,070
much longer than is necessary for

484
00:17:48,070 --> 00:17:50,340
the protons to still be here.

485
00:17:50,980 --> 00:17:53,100
The mean lifetime of a proton is

486
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:55,220
more than 10 to the 32 years,

487
00:17:55,220 --> 00:17:56,020
so it's very long.

488
00:17:56,820 --> 00:17:58,780
And we don't completely understand why.

489
00:17:58,940 --> 00:17:59,180
In fact,

490
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:00,380
we don't understand why at all.

491
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:01,600
But we take it as a fact.

492
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:03,040
A fact,

493
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,600
at least a temporary fact.

494
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,300
Let's assume it for the moment.

495
00:18:08,580 --> 00:18:11,250
That would mean that the

496
00:18:11,250 --> 00:18:13,920
total baryon number in the universe,

497
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:16,280
but let's just say in a box,

498
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,020
in a box,

499
00:18:18,020 --> 00:18:19,560
doesn't change.

500
00:18:20,340 --> 00:18:23,630
And so the only theory of this excess that we could

501
00:18:23,630 --> 00:18:26,920
have is that it was built in from the very beginning

502
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:28,580
and it still survives today.

503
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:32,360
That would be a consequence of baryon conservation,

504
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:34,480
baryon number conservation.

505
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:36,100
I'm not saying that's true.

506
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:39,520
I'm saying that's a consequence of baryon conservation,

507
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,850
that this is the same today

508
00:18:41,850 --> 00:18:43,780
as it was at the very beginning.

509
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:45,420
Now,

510
00:18:45,420 --> 00:18:48,100
there's another symmetry of nature.

511
00:18:50,340 --> 00:18:50,900
Which again,

512
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:52,980
is not really a symmetry of nature.

513
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,820
But you might have thought about

514
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:56,440
it as a symmetry of nature.

515
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:59,940
At the time that Sakharov put out his theory,

516
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:02,530
it was only a couple of years after

517
00:19:02,530 --> 00:19:04,760
it was discovered that it wasn't a symmetry.

518
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:06,420
We'll talk about it.

519
00:19:06,820 --> 00:19:11,000
But it's particle-antiparticle reflection symmetry.

520
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:13,320
The statement that particles,

521
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:15,960
if interchanged with antiparticles,

522
00:19:16,220 --> 00:19:18,420
that you can't tell the difference.

523
00:19:18,939 --> 00:19:19,820
Of course,

524
00:19:19,820 --> 00:19:21,100
you can tell the difference

525
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:22,380
between a proton and an antiproton,

526
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:24,400
because we're made out of protons.

527
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:29,880
But if we changed all of our protons to antiprotons,

528
00:19:30,860 --> 00:19:33,620
if you were made out of antiprotons,

529
00:19:33,620 --> 00:19:34,660
and I was made out of protons,

530
00:19:34,860 --> 00:19:35,760
don't get too close to me,

531
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:39,780
and somebody showed me a proton,

532
00:19:40,260 --> 00:19:41,100
I would say,

533
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:41,400
yes,

534
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:41,960
that's a proton.

535
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,720
Somebody showed you an antiproton,

536
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,240
you would have exactly the same response.

537
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:45,720
I mean,

538
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:48,400
you would see the same thing.

539
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,360
You would see the same thing that I saw.

540
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:53,620
That's called particle-antiparticle symmetry,

541
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:54,380
or reflection,

542
00:19:54,380 --> 00:19:56,380
charge-reflection symmetry.

543
00:19:58,220 --> 00:20:04,000
And for technical reasons,

544
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:04,940
well,

545
00:20:04,940 --> 00:20:07,020
alright,

546
00:20:07,020 --> 00:20:07,960
that's a symmetry.

547
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,620
It's not a symmetry.

548
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:13,460
But up until around 1964 or 65,

549
00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:14,700
I forget exactly when,

550
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:18,380
it was thought that charge conjugation,

551
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:23,880
this is called C equals charge conjugation symmetry,

552
00:20:27,540 --> 00:20:29,980
it was believed that it was a symmetry.

553
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,740
Particles go to antiparticles.

554
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,270
Two other things which were

555
00:20:35,270 --> 00:20:37,140
thought to be symmetries of nature,

556
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:38,740
which went along with this,

557
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:40,120
were called P,

558
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:43,180
which is P is for parity,

559
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:48,260
but it has nothing to do with,

560
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:51,100
it's not a symmetry of nature economics or fairness.

561
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:54,460
It's left-right symmetry,

562
00:20:54,460 --> 00:20:56,900
mirror-reflection symmetry,

563
00:20:59,179 --> 00:21:02,809
that if there's a kind

564
00:21:02,809 --> 00:21:06,440
of particle which exhibits a handedness,

565
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:07,560
for example,

566
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:10,640
it rotates to the right when it moves forward,

567
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:13,220
spins to the right when it moves forward,

568
00:21:13,420 --> 00:21:16,540
then it had been assumed that there would be

569
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,960
a vertical which also moves forward,

570
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:21,680
left-right symmetry,

571
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:24,560
and that was called parity.

572
00:21:26,180 --> 00:21:29,960
And the final interesting symmetry for us tonight

573
