00:53:54,140 --> 00:53:55,220
Hot enough to...

1420
00:53:55,940 --> 00:53:57,820
What I need to explain to you

1421
00:53:58,620 --> 00:54:01,500
is first why this can happen rapidly,

1422
00:54:01,500 --> 00:54:04,280
even though I said that the proton is very stable.

1423
00:54:04,940 --> 00:54:06,420
It has to do with the environment.

1424
00:54:08,400 --> 00:54:09,980
Let me come back to it.

1425
00:54:10,120 --> 00:54:10,800
It's a good question.

1426
00:54:11,120 --> 00:54:11,580
All right.

1427
00:54:12,680 --> 00:54:17,380
How do we overcome the fact

1428
00:54:17,380 --> 00:54:19,920
that the proton is so incredibly stable?

1429
00:54:20,120 --> 00:54:20,820
Remember what I said.

1430
00:54:20,900 --> 00:54:23,980
The proton lifetime is something like

1431
00:54:23,980 --> 00:54:25,160
about 10 to the 33,

1432
00:54:25,160 --> 00:54:27,160
10 to the 34 years or longer.

1433
00:54:27,840 --> 00:54:29,580
The universe has only been around

1434
00:54:29,580 --> 00:54:31,300
for 10 to the 10th years.

1435
00:54:32,300 --> 00:54:34,060
So on that scale,

1436
00:54:34,320 --> 00:54:36,100
the proton is very stable,

1437
00:54:36,280 --> 00:54:37,740
and why don't we get

1438
00:54:37,740 --> 00:54:39,200
to ignore this kind of thing?

1439
00:54:39,800 --> 00:54:41,820
And the reason has to do with the fact

1440
00:54:41,820 --> 00:54:44,000
that the universe in its very early stages

1441
00:54:44,000 --> 00:54:44,740
was very,

1442
00:54:44,740 --> 00:54:45,420
very hot.

1443
00:54:46,420 --> 00:54:48,180
Because it was very hot,

1444
00:54:48,900 --> 00:54:49,900
the protons,

1445
00:54:49,900 --> 00:54:51,360
or the quarks in particular,

1446
00:54:51,520 --> 00:54:52,860
we can substitute quarks here,

1447
00:54:52,860 --> 00:54:53,460
it doesn't matter,

1448
00:54:53,600 --> 00:54:55,460
because it was very hot,

1449
00:54:55,600 --> 00:54:57,240
they were constantly engaged

1450
00:54:57,240 --> 00:54:58,040
in very,

1451
00:54:58,040 --> 00:54:59,280
very high energy collisions.

1452
00:55:00,460 --> 00:55:01,480
The high energy collisions

1453
00:55:01,500 --> 00:55:05,200
meant that the protons moving in this plasma,

1454
00:55:05,360 --> 00:55:06,500
in this very hot gas,

1455
00:55:06,860 --> 00:55:08,640
had lots of energy.

1456
00:55:09,420 --> 00:55:10,640
How much energy?

1457
00:55:10,820 --> 00:55:12,140
It depends on the temperature.

1458
00:55:13,320 --> 00:55:14,840
But at some temperature,

1459
00:55:15,080 --> 00:55:17,400
you get to a high enough point

1460
00:55:19,620 --> 00:55:21,740
where the average kinetic energy,

1461
00:55:21,860 --> 00:55:24,820
the average extra excitation on energy of the proton,

1462
00:55:25,100 --> 00:55:26,480
is high enough

1463
00:55:26,480 --> 00:55:29,600
so that even these heavy particles here

1464
00:55:29,600 --> 00:55:31,260
do not suppress

1465
00:55:31,500 --> 00:55:32,860
the proton decay,

1466
00:55:33,060 --> 00:55:34,200
or the baryon violation.

1467
00:55:34,740 --> 00:55:35,880
In other words,

1468
00:55:35,880 --> 00:55:36,600
to put it short,

1469
00:55:37,360 --> 00:55:40,280
a proton at rest,

1470
00:55:42,440 --> 00:55:43,620
forget at rest,

1471
00:55:52,740 --> 00:55:55,420
a proton in an environment

1472
00:55:56,500 --> 00:55:59,340
where it isn't constantly being knocked around

1473
00:55:59,340 --> 00:56:01,160
and having an enormously,

1474
00:56:01,500 --> 00:56:02,880
largely large excess energy

1475
00:56:02,880 --> 00:56:03,980
of some kind or another,

1476
00:56:04,140 --> 00:56:05,660
is very stable.

1477
00:56:06,240 --> 00:56:08,240
But when it's heated up to a high temperature,

1478
00:56:08,520 --> 00:56:10,260
a high enough temperature,

1479
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:12,620
this excess mass here

1480
00:56:12,620 --> 00:56:14,660
is not an important factor,

1481
00:56:14,780 --> 00:56:16,760
and the proton decay would happen quickly.

1482
00:56:18,160 --> 00:56:20,960
So if we go back to the very early universe,

1483
00:56:21,060 --> 00:56:22,720
when the temperature was very hot,

1484
00:56:25,640 --> 00:56:30,620
then these kind of processes can happen.

1485
00:56:30,620 --> 00:56:31,180
Now,

1486
00:56:31,180 --> 00:56:34,880
this statement that the total decay rate

1487
00:56:35,620 --> 00:56:38,820
is the same for protons and antiprotons

1488
00:56:38,820 --> 00:56:41,180
is a statement about zero temperature.

1489
00:56:41,500 --> 00:56:45,040
It's a statement about a proton at rest

1490
00:56:45,040 --> 00:56:47,680
in an environment where it has no excess energy.

1491
00:56:48,280 --> 00:56:49,900
When it's being kicked around,

1492
00:56:50,200 --> 00:56:52,420
and when it has extra energy,

1493
00:56:52,700 --> 00:56:55,900
then that is not necessarily the case.

1494
00:56:56,200 --> 00:56:57,040
In fact,

1495
00:56:57,040 --> 00:56:58,140
it's generally not the case.

1496
00:56:58,360 --> 00:57:00,600
In an environment which has some energy,

1497
00:57:00,620 --> 00:57:02,740
which is kicking the protons around,

1498
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:05,620
the decay rates don't have to be the same.

1499
00:57:06,040 --> 00:57:06,460
So...

1500
00:57:12,280 --> 00:57:14,220
So that is not a problem.

1501
00:57:14,600 --> 00:57:17,760
The problem has to do with the CPT symmetry.

1502
00:57:19,660 --> 00:57:23,420
I said that there was no particle inversion symmetry,

1503
00:57:23,640 --> 00:57:25,260
but there is a symmetry,

1504
00:57:26,540 --> 00:57:29,420
at least in all known quantum field theories,

1505
00:57:31,500 --> 00:57:32,700
string theories,

1506
00:57:32,700 --> 00:57:34,280
any theory we know how to write down,

1507
00:57:34,480 --> 00:57:38,060
which has relativity and quantum mechanics built into it.

1508
00:57:38,500 --> 00:57:42,440
Charge conjugation times reflection times time reversal.

1509
00:57:42,920 --> 00:57:43,520
Again,

1510
00:57:43,520 --> 00:57:46,640
what that means is you exchange every particle

1511
00:57:46,640 --> 00:57:47,620
for its antiparticle,

1512
00:57:47,620 --> 00:57:49,020
you reflect in a mirror,

1513
00:57:49,140 --> 00:57:50,720
and you run the film backward.

1514
00:57:51,640 --> 00:57:54,820
That is a symmetry of all theories.

1515
00:57:55,520 --> 00:57:56,260
All right.

1516
00:57:56,700 --> 00:57:57,300
So...

1517
00:57:58,620 --> 00:57:59,400
What is the answer to this?

1518
00:57:59,400 --> 00:57:59,740
What does that mean?

1519
00:57:59,860 --> 00:58:00,460
That means,

1520
00:58:00,460 --> 00:58:01,640
among other things,

1521
00:58:02,400 --> 00:58:04,920
that in thermal equilibrium,

1522
00:58:05,640 --> 00:58:08,200
if the universe was just static,

1523
00:58:08,440 --> 00:58:09,720
if it wasn't changing,

1524
00:58:09,720 --> 00:58:10,640
but it was hot,

1525
00:58:11,339 --> 00:58:12,620
in thermal equilibrium,

1526
00:58:13,520 --> 00:58:15,180
in thermal equilibrium,

1527
00:58:16,340 --> 00:58:18,980
forward time is the same as backward time.

1528
00:58:19,160 --> 00:58:20,160
In thermal equilibrium,

1529
00:58:21,340 --> 00:58:24,700
backward and forward and time are the same thing.

1530
00:58:25,000 --> 00:58:28,420
There is no asymmetry of time reversal.

1531
00:58:29,400 --> 00:58:30,880
So in thermal equilibrium,

1532
00:58:31,080 --> 00:58:32,680
where the universe is not changing,

1533
00:58:32,880 --> 00:58:34,140
an imaginary universe,

1534
00:58:34,140 --> 00:58:35,260
which is just a pot,

1535
00:58:35,340 --> 00:58:36,020
which is there,

1536
00:58:36,020 --> 00:58:36,480
hot,

1537
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:37,920
a hot pot,

1538
00:58:39,580 --> 00:58:42,060
it would have time reversal symmetry.

1539
00:58:42,620 --> 00:58:44,720
If it has time reversal symmetry,

1540
00:58:44,980 --> 00:58:48,260
and it has C times P times T,

1541
00:58:49,120 --> 00:58:52,800
then it must have C-P symmetry.

1542
00:58:53,980 --> 00:58:54,760
All right.

1543
00:58:55,140 --> 00:58:58,100
C-P just means particle change to antiparticle

1544
00:58:58,100 --> 00:58:58,880
for our purposes.

1545
00:58:58,880 --> 00:59:01,340
If particle goes to antiparticle

1546
00:59:01,340 --> 00:59:02,520
and time goes to...

1547
00:59:02,520 --> 00:59:04,300
I was going to say anti-time,

1548
00:59:04,400 --> 00:59:05,880
and time goes to minus time,

1549
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:06,880
if that's a good symmetry,

1550
00:59:07,140 --> 00:59:09,180
but the world has no

1551
00:59:09,180 --> 00:59:11,220
bias toward one time or another,

1552
00:59:11,600 --> 00:59:13,760
then you're stuck again.

1553
00:59:13,920 --> 00:59:19,300
You're back to having a particle-antiparticle symmetry,

1554
00:59:19,540 --> 00:59:25,560
and you cannot have a proton-antiproton excess

1555
00:59:25,560 --> 00:59:27,540
in thermal equilibrium.

1556
00:59:27,540 --> 00:59:28,340
That's a theorem.

1557
00:59:28,800 --> 00:59:31,380
That's a theorem that's been known for a long time,

1558
00:59:31,560 --> 00:59:34,180
that in thermal equilibrium,

1559
00:59:35,160 --> 00:59:38,480
that the thermal equilibrium will come to a configuration

1560
00:59:38,480 --> 00:59:39,980
with equal numbers of protons.

1561
00:59:40,120 --> 00:59:42,080
But the universe was not in thermal equilibrium

1562
00:59:42,080 --> 00:59:42,960
at early times.

1563
00:59:43,060 --> 00:59:43,860
It was expanding,

1564
00:59:44,460 --> 00:59:47,940
and it was expanding fast at early times.

1565
00:59:48,180 --> 00:59:50,360
It was expanding fast enough

1566
00:59:51,140 --> 00:59:53,680
that it could not be considered an equilibrium.

1567
00:59:54,620 --> 00:59:56,180
If it's not an equilibrium,

1568
00:59:56,180 --> 00:59:58,300
that means that forward time

1569
00:59:58,300 --> 01:00:00,420
and backward time are different.

1570
01:00:00,660 --> 01:00:01,760
That's the reason.

1571
01:00:01,940 --> 01:00:02,940
If the universe is expanding,

1572
01:00:03,080 --> 01:00:07,000
forward time and backward time are not the same.

1573
01:00:07,320 --> 01:00:12,220
So in a rapidly expanding phase of the universe,

1574
01:00:12,540 --> 01:00:15,160
we don't have to worry about time symmetry.

1575
01:00:15,400 --> 01:00:17,020
It is definitely not symmetric.

1576
01:00:18,020 --> 01:00:19,900
If time symmetry is broken

1577
01:00:19,900 --> 01:00:22,140
just by the expansion of the universe,

1578
01:00:22,420 --> 01:00:23,520
then we're in business.

1579
01:00:23,920 --> 01:00:25,680
Then we have...

1580
01:00:26,180 --> 01:00:29,480
enough asymmetry of all possible kinds

1581
01:00:30,180 --> 01:00:35,140
that the baryon violation allows a change

1582
01:00:35,140 --> 01:00:36,940
in the baryon number.

1583
01:00:37,120 --> 01:00:41,680
The CP violation allows a directionality for it,

1584
01:00:41,740 --> 01:00:43,540
and the...

1585
01:00:48,060 --> 01:00:49,360
out of equilibrium.

1586
01:00:49,760 --> 01:00:51,020
Out of equilibrium.

1587
01:00:53,080 --> 01:00:54,120
Yeah.

1588
01:00:56,180 --> 01:00:57,860
This means things are changing rapidly

1589
01:00:58,980 --> 01:01:00,800
in a particular direction of time.

1590
01:01:01,300 --> 01:01:04,600
It means the universe is expanding fast enough...

1591
01:01:05,000 --> 01:01:05,820
That's all it means.

1592
01:01:06,340 --> 01:01:09,020
So that running the thing backwards

1593
01:01:09,020 --> 01:01:11,240
does not look like the original thing.

1594
01:01:11,780 --> 01:01:13,720
In a world where the

1595
01:01:13,720 --> 01:01:15,660
universe is running in one way,

1596
01:01:15,740 --> 01:01:16,900
namely expanding,

1597
01:01:18,580 --> 01:01:20,460
it is out of equilibrium.

1598
01:01:22,420 --> 01:01:23,760
Being out of equ...

1599
01:01:23,760 --> 01:01:25,980
It has to be enough out of equilibrium.

1600
01:01:26,320 --> 01:01:28,100
It's not enough for it to be very,

1601
01:01:28,100 --> 01:01:29,560
very slowly expanding.

1602
01:01:29,860 --> 01:01:32,600
It has to be expanding rapidly enough

1603
01:01:32,600 --> 01:01:35,040
that these microscopic processes

1604
01:01:35,040 --> 01:01:37,600
don't have a time to adjust themselves

1605
01:01:38,660 --> 01:01:41,140
to the equilibrium configuration.

1606
01:01:41,700 --> 01:01:43,620
But whatever it means,

1607
01:01:43,700 --> 01:01:47,340
it means that backward and forward times are different.

1608
01:01:47,880 --> 01:01:50,660
That a picture of the universe...

1609
01:01:50,660 --> 01:01:52,800
that a movie of the universe

1610
01:01:53,760 --> 01:01:56,780
allows you to tell which way is forward in time

1611
01:01:56,780 --> 01:01:58,420
and which way is backward in time.

1612
01:01:58,620 --> 01:02:00,440
Just by the expansion.

1613
01:02:01,500 --> 01:02:02,980
And the fact that it's cooling.

1614
01:02:03,140 --> 01:02:06,040
The fact that early times it suddenly cooled...

1615
01:02:07,140 --> 01:02:11,020
It suddenly cooled rather rapidly in the beginning.

1616
01:02:11,380 --> 01:02:14,480
That's enough to completely ruin

1617
01:02:14,480 --> 01:02:16,600
the time reversal symmetry.

1618
01:02:17,720 --> 01:02:20,480
And if the time reversal symmetry is ruined,

1619
01:02:20,740 --> 01:02:23,480
the CP symmetry is also going to be ruined.

1620
01:02:26,140 --> 01:02:26,700
So,

1621
01:02:26,700 --> 01:02:29,580
those were the three conditions of Sakharov.

1622
01:02:30,120 --> 01:02:31,950
All three are believed to be

1623
01:02:31,950 --> 01:02:33,780
really satisfied in the real world.

1624
01:02:34,660 --> 01:02:36,960
And it's also believed that they are enough

1625
01:02:37,480 --> 01:02:39,540
that if all three of these are true,

1626
01:02:39,800 --> 01:02:41,560
that there's really just no way

1627
01:02:41,560 --> 01:02:43,400
it would be a complete accident

1628
01:02:43,400 --> 01:02:45,700
with no rationale to it

1629
01:02:45,700 --> 01:02:47,540
if there wasn't some...

1630
01:02:48,640 --> 01:02:50,540
some excess created.

1631
01:02:52,840 --> 01:02:53,460
The problem is that

1632
01:02:53,460 --> 01:02:58,160
nobody knows enough about the physics of the early universe

1633
01:02:58,160 --> 01:03:00,840
and the physics of very high energy collisions,

1634
01:03:01,240 --> 01:03:02,760
the physics of very,

1635
01:03:02,760 --> 01:03:03,720
very hot temperature,

1636
01:03:04,040 --> 01:03:06,800
the nature of the particles that are in here,

1637
01:03:07,040 --> 01:03:09,480
the details of what drives

1638
01:03:09,480 --> 01:03:11,920
the CP violation and so forth.

1639
01:03:12,280 --> 01:03:14,320
Nobody knows enough about it

1640
01:03:14,320 --> 01:03:16,440
to be able to make a calculation

1641
01:03:16,440 --> 01:03:19,400
of what the imbalance is

1642
01:03:19,400 --> 01:03:22,120
of protons to antiprotons.

1643
01:03:22,220 --> 01:03:23,440
That simply we don't know.

1644
01:03:23,440 --> 01:03:23,800
We don't know enough.

1645
01:03:23,940 --> 01:03:25,100
So what we know

1646
01:03:25,100 --> 01:03:28,520
is all three ingredients that are both necessary

1647
01:03:28,520 --> 01:03:29,640
and probably sufficient

1648
01:03:29,640 --> 01:03:32,180
to explain an imbalance,

1649
01:03:32,600 --> 01:03:33,460
those are there,

1650
01:03:33,660 --> 01:03:36,680
but the ingredients needed to make a computation

1651
01:03:37,360 --> 01:03:38,280
