2962
01:46:22,400 --> 01:46:24,680
is through Lagrange's equations.

2963
01:46:25,380 --> 01:46:25,860
Lagrange's equations are the following.

2964
01:46:25,860 --> 01:46:26,500
Lagrangian,

2965
01:46:26,500 --> 01:46:28,380
let's write the Lagrangian now.

2966
01:46:28,620 --> 01:46:31,080
The Lagrangian is the difference

2967
01:46:31,080 --> 01:46:33,500
of kinetic energy and potential energy.

2968
01:46:33,960 --> 01:46:34,420
So,

2969
01:46:34,420 --> 01:46:37,080
you pick up your copy of the theoretical minimum

2970
01:46:37,400 --> 01:46:39,820
and you look up Lagrange's equations

2971
01:46:42,259 --> 01:46:43,300
with this.

2972
01:46:44,240 --> 01:46:46,100
Phi is like the coordinate,

2973
01:46:46,420 --> 01:46:47,680
phi is like the coordinate,

2974
01:46:47,980 --> 01:46:49,780
and here is the Lagrangian.

2975
01:46:50,320 --> 01:46:53,380
The only new thing that wouldn't be there

2976
01:46:53,380 --> 01:46:54,940
for an ordinary particle

2977
01:46:56,000 --> 01:46:57,460
is this A of t.

2978
01:46:58,580 --> 01:46:59,400
All right,

2979
01:46:59,400 --> 01:47:01,060
so let's work out Lagrange's equations.

2980
01:47:01,880 --> 01:47:04,840
The first term is d by dt,

2981
01:47:05,900 --> 01:47:07,900
or I suppose we can make it...

2982
01:47:09,380 --> 01:47:13,420
d by dt of partial of L

2983
01:47:13,420 --> 01:47:16,280
with respect to phi dot.

2984
01:47:16,440 --> 01:47:17,260
Everybody remember that?

2985
01:47:19,440 --> 01:47:21,240
And what's on the right-hand side?

2986
01:47:24,120 --> 01:47:24,760
Right.

2987
01:47:27,180 --> 01:47:28,420
That's Lagrange's equations.

2988
01:47:29,060 --> 01:47:29,540
So,

2989
01:47:29,540 --> 01:47:32,020
partial of L with respect to phi dot...

2990
01:47:33,440 --> 01:47:35,480
This is the equation that we get out of it.

2991
01:47:35,540 --> 01:47:37,180
Partial of L with respect to phi dot

2992
01:47:37,180 --> 01:47:38,040
is just phi dot,

2993
01:47:39,680 --> 01:47:41,500
times A cubed of t.

2994
01:47:44,620 --> 01:47:48,160
This is partial of L with respect to phi dot.

2995
01:47:48,200 --> 01:47:49,760
This isn't here.

2996
01:47:50,400 --> 01:47:51,740
dL by d phi dot

2997
01:47:51,740 --> 01:47:54,500
is phi dot times A cubed of t.

2998
01:47:54,560 --> 01:47:55,020
Is that obvious?

2999
01:47:55,860 --> 01:47:56,460
Good.

3000
01:47:56,720 --> 01:47:59,420
Now we have to take its time derivative,

3001
01:47:59,680 --> 01:48:00,620
d by dt.

3002
01:48:03,980 --> 01:48:06,220
And that we have to set equal

3003
01:48:06,860 --> 01:48:08,060
to A cubed

3004
01:48:13,239 --> 01:48:15,240
