01:48:46,960 --> 01:48:48,560
So let's work it out and see what it is.

3019
01:48:49,060 --> 01:48:49,940
First of all,

3020
01:48:49,940 --> 01:48:50,700
the d by dt,

3021
01:48:51,820 --> 01:48:53,040
there are two terms.

3022
01:48:53,300 --> 01:48:55,120
One comes from hitting phi dot.

3023
01:48:55,120 --> 01:48:56,840
The other comes from hitting A cubed.

3024
01:48:57,140 --> 01:48:59,040
So let's first do the first one.

3025
01:48:59,120 --> 01:49:01,300
The first one is A cubed

3026
01:49:01,980 --> 01:49:03,180
times phi double dot.

3027
01:49:04,580 --> 01:49:06,900
That's d by dt of phi dot

3028
01:49:06,900 --> 01:49:08,340
times A cubed.

3029
01:49:08,680 --> 01:49:09,760
And what's the second term?

3030
01:49:11,360 --> 01:49:12,500
It's phi dot

3031
01:49:14,799 --> 01:49:17,300
times the time derivative of A cubed.

3032
01:49:18,080 --> 01:49:18,680
Okay?

3033
01:49:18,760 --> 01:49:20,720
The time derivative of A cubed

3034
01:49:20,720 --> 01:49:21,740
is

3035
01:49:21,740 --> 01:49:22,920
three

3036
01:49:22,920 --> 01:49:24,680
A squared

3037
01:49:25,580 --> 01:49:27,120
times A dot.

3038
01:49:28,660 --> 01:49:29,780
Do I have that right?

3039
01:49:30,660 --> 01:49:30,960
Yeah.

3040
01:49:31,240 --> 01:49:33,600
That's in a parenthesis over here.

3041
01:49:34,480 --> 01:49:35,740
And that's equal,

3042
01:49:35,960 --> 01:49:37,640
let's just call it,

3043
01:49:37,680 --> 01:49:40,160
to A cubed times the force.

3044
01:49:41,520 --> 01:49:43,260
The force on phi.

3045
01:49:46,560 --> 01:49:47,160
Okay.

3046
01:49:48,240 --> 01:49:49,400
It's very tempting,

3047
01:49:49,400 --> 01:49:50,360
and I will do it,

3048
01:49:50,400 --> 01:49:52,300
to divide out the A cubed,

3049
01:49:52,920 --> 01:49:54,080
because it appears both here and here.

3050
01:49:55,060 --> 01:49:56,840
Let's divide out the A cubed.

3051
01:49:59,580 --> 01:50:01,640
But I better divide over here also,

3052
01:50:01,640 --> 01:50:01,880
huh?

3053
01:50:03,780 --> 01:50:04,420
Okay.

3054
01:50:08,180 --> 01:50:10,200
So let's clean it up.

3055
01:50:10,820 --> 01:50:12,460
It's phi double dot

3056
01:50:13,579 --> 01:50:14,860
plus three

3057
01:50:16,120 --> 01:50:18,040
A dot over A,

3058
01:50:20,919 --> 01:50:24,180
A squared divided by A cubed is one over A,

3059
01:50:24,420 --> 01:50:25,920
so it's A dot over A

3060
01:50:26,779 --> 01:50:28,200
times phi dot

3061
01:50:29,360 --> 01:50:30,660
is equal to F.

3062
01:50:32,700 --> 01:50:35,160
What is A dot over A called in cosmology?

3063
01:50:36,700 --> 01:50:37,880
The Hubble constant,

3064
01:50:38,060 --> 01:50:39,600
which is not generally a constant,

3065
01:50:39,820 --> 01:50:41,020
but it's H.

3066
01:50:41,960 --> 01:50:43,320
It's of course...

3067
01:50:43,320 --> 01:50:45,480
It's supposed to be like the same everywhere,

3068
01:50:45,480 --> 01:50:45,860
though?

3069
01:50:46,380 --> 01:50:47,260
Everywhere's in space,

3070
01:50:47,260 --> 01:50:49,080
but not necessarily in time.

3071
01:50:49,680 --> 01:50:51,040
Maybe the same in time,

3072
01:50:51,100 --> 01:50:51,860
but it may not be.

3073
01:50:52,760 --> 01:50:53,340
All right.

3074
01:50:53,360 --> 01:50:55,340
So we'll come back to what it is in time,

3075
01:50:55,380 --> 01:50:56,160
but keep in mind,

3076
01:50:56,200 --> 01:50:57,360
it could be time dependent.

3077
01:50:59,120 --> 01:51:00,000
A double...

3078
01:51:00,000 --> 01:51:00,360
Sorry,

3079
01:51:00,360 --> 01:51:01,340
not A double dot,

3080
01:51:01,420 --> 01:51:02,100
phi double dot.

3081
01:51:03,700 --> 01:51:05,720
Phi double dot from here

3082
01:51:06,440 --> 01:51:10,280
plus three H times phi dot equals F.

3083
01:51:16,000 --> 01:51:17,240
Let's write this one this way.

3084
01:51:17,240 --> 01:51:18,040
Plus...

3085
01:51:20,120 --> 01:51:21,720
equals F.

3086
01:51:23,400 --> 01:51:25,900
This is exactly the same equation

3087
01:51:25,900 --> 01:51:27,920
as the falling stone

3088
01:51:29,960 --> 01:51:32,480
with a viscosity coefficient three H

3089
01:51:33,240 --> 01:51:36,060
and a force which is just a gradient of V.

3090
01:51:37,820 --> 01:51:42,080
So our model for the way this field evolves

3091
01:51:43,000 --> 01:51:44,920
can be envisioned

3092
01:51:47,240 --> 01:51:48,600
by just supposing

3093
01:51:49,440 --> 01:51:51,860
that phi was the position

3094
01:51:51,860 --> 01:51:54,280
of a particle on a hill

3095
01:51:55,120 --> 01:51:57,320
where the height of the hill was V,

3096
01:51:58,880 --> 01:52:02,360
where the gradient of the altitude of the hill

3097
01:52:02,360 --> 01:52:03,260
was the force,

3098
01:52:04,200 --> 01:52:04,980
dV d phi,

3099
01:52:06,900 --> 01:52:09,140
a ball rolling down the hill,

3100
01:52:10,299 --> 01:52:14,040
except that there's a viscous drag force

3101
01:52:14,940 --> 01:52:17,120
proportional to the Hubble expansion rate,

3102
01:52:18,040 --> 01:52:18,720
which is the force of the hill.

3103
01:52:18,720 --> 01:52:20,080
So the Hubble expansion rate

3104
01:52:20,960 --> 01:52:23,140
behaves as a kind of friction.

3105
01:52:24,460 --> 01:52:27,720
That is why we went through this exercise over here.

3106
01:52:28,300 --> 01:52:33,640
If the Hubble friction is strong,

3107
01:52:33,980 --> 01:52:35,760
if H is big,

3108
01:52:35,860 --> 01:52:37,800
and the force here,

3109
01:52:37,940 --> 01:52:41,100
and if the hill is reasonably flat,

3110
01:52:41,200 --> 01:52:42,560
not terribly flat,

3111
01:52:42,740 --> 01:52:44,040
but somewhat flat,

3112
01:52:45,700 --> 01:52:46,380
then...

3113
01:52:46,380 --> 01:52:49,720
this could be like a ball moving through

3114
01:52:52,259 --> 01:52:55,620
motor oil in Wisconsin on a cold day.

3115
01:52:56,320 --> 01:52:56,620
Okay?

3116
01:52:58,419 --> 01:53:00,660
It's just left to its own devices

3117
01:53:00,660 --> 01:53:02,000
